Arthropodologist
One who studies arthropods(arthropod jointed leg or part of a foot).  Though "arthropodologist" does not arrive in some dictionary searches, it is in interpretation of the combination of "arthropod/o-" plus "logist".

An entomologist, however, is one who studies insects, a member of the arthropod phylum.  Arthropods include:  insects(class Insecta), arachnids(class Arachnida), and crustaceans(class Crustacea).
Similar terms not known to be technically accurate:  arachnidologist and crustaceologist.

I take some information from a reliable source:  Merriam-Webster's 11th Collegiate Dictionary.